INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` VALUES (1,1,'Prepare the jerk marinade by blending together scotch bonnet peppers, green onions, garlic, ginger, thyme, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg, soy sauce, brown sugar, lime juice, and olive oil in a food processor or blender until smooth.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(1,2,'Place the chicken pieces in a large bowl or resealable plastic bag, and pour the marinade over them. Make sure the chicken is well coated with the marinade. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight, to allow the flavors to meld.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(1,3,'Preheat your grill to medium-high heat. If using a charcoal grill, set up for indirect grilling.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(1,4,'Remove the chicken from the marinade and let any excess drip off.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(1,5,'Grill the chicken over direct heat for 5-7 minutes per side, until nicely charred and cooked through. Alternatively, you can bake the chicken in a preheated oven at 375°F (190°C) for about 30-40 minutes, or until cooked through.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(1,6,'Once cooked, remove the chicken from the grill or oven and let it rest for a few minutes before serving.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(1,7,'Serve the Jamaican Jerk Chicken hot with rice and peas, or your favorite side dishes.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(2,1,'Cook the pasta according to the package instructions until al dente. Drain and rinse under cold water to stop the cooking process. Transfer to a large mixing bowl.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,2,'Add chopped vegetables such as bell peppers, cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, red onions, and olives to the bowl with the cooked pasta.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,3,'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, red wine vinegar, Dijon mustard, garlic, salt, and black pepper to make the dressing.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,4,'Pour the dressing over the pasta and vegetables, and toss until everything is evenly coated.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,5,'Add in additional ingredients such as cubed cheese, cooked chicken or ham, and fresh herbs like basil or parsley if desired.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,6,'Cover the pasta salad and refrigerate for at least 1 hour to allow the flavors to meld together.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,7,'Before serving, taste and adjust the seasoning if necessary. You can also add a splash of lemon juice or more olive oil if the salad seems dry.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(2,8,'Serve the pasta salad chilled as a side dish or a light meal.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,1,'Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,2,'In a large pot, bring salted water to a boil and cook the lasagna noodles according to the package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,3,'In a large skillet, cook ground beef or Italian sausage over medium heat until browned. Drain excess fat if necessary.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,4,'Add diced onions, minced garlic, and chopped bell peppers to the skillet with the cooked meat. Cook until the vegetables are softened.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,5,'Stir in canned crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, salt, and black pepper. Simmer the sauce for about 10-15 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld together.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,6,'In a separate bowl, mix together ricotta cheese, grated Parmesan cheese, chopped fresh parsley, and one beaten egg until well combined.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,7,'Spread a thin layer of the meat sauce on the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish. Place a layer of cooked lasagna noodles over the sauce.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,8,'Spread half of the ricotta cheese mixture over the noodles, followed by a layer of shredded mozzarella cheese.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,9,'Repeat the layers - meat sauce, noodles, ricotta mixture, and mozzarella cheese.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,10,'Cover the baking dish with aluminum foil and bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,11,'Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 15 minutes, or until the cheese is bubbly and golden brown.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(3,12,'Let the lasagna cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,1,'In a large mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour, baking powder, salt, and a sweetener of your choice, such as sugar or honey.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,2,'In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, and melted butter or oil until well combined.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,3,'Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Be careful not to overmix; a few lumps are okay.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,4,'If desired, add in additional ingredients such as mashed bananas, blueberries, chopped nuts, or chocolate chips for extra flavor and texture.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,5,'Heat a lightly greased skillet or griddle over medium heat. Pour a ladleful of batter onto the skillet for each pancake.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,6,'Cook until bubbles form on the surface of the pancake and the edges begin to look set, then flip and cook until golden brown on the other side.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,7,'Repeat with the remaining batter, adding more oil or butter to the skillet as needed.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(4,8,'Serve the hearty pancakes warm with your favorite toppings, such as maple syrup, fresh fruit, yogurt, or whipped cream.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(5,1,'Cook the couscous according to the package instructions. Fluff with a fork and set aside to cool.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,2,'In a large mixing bowl, combine the cooked couscous with diced cucumbers, cherry tomatoes (halved), diced bell peppers (assorted colors), sliced red onions, chopped fresh parsley, and crumbled feta cheese.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,3,'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, salt, and black pepper to make the dressing.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,4,'Pour the dressing over the couscous and vegetables, and toss until everything is well coated.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,5,'Taste and adjust the seasoning if necessary. You can add more salt, pepper, or lemon juice according to your preference.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,6,'Cover the salad and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld together.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,7,'Before serving, garnish the salad with additional chopped parsley and feta cheese, if desired.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(5,8,'Serve the Summer Garden Couscous Salad chilled as a side dish or a light meal.','2024-05-06 21:49:52'),(6,1,'In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced onions and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,2,'Add diced carrots, celery, and minced garlic to the pot. Cook for an additional 3-4 minutes until vegetables are slightly tender.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,3,'Stir in diced yellow squash and cook for another 5 minutes, allowing the squash to soften slightly.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,4,'Sprinkle flour over the vegetables and stir to coat. Cook for 2 minutes to remove the raw flour taste.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,5,'Slowly pour in vegetable broth, stirring constantly to prevent lumps from forming.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,6,'Add diced potatoes, corn kernels (fresh or frozen), dried thyme, salt, and black pepper to the pot. Bring the mixture to a simmer.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,7,'Cover and cook for 15-20 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,8,'Stir in heavy cream and chopped fresh parsley. Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,9,'Remove from heat and let the chowder cool slightly before serving.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,10,'Garnish with additional parsley and a sprinkle of paprika if desired.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(6,11,'Serve the Squash Corn Chowder hot with crusty bread or crackers.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,1,'Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,2,'Add minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,3,'Stir in canned white beans (such as cannellini beans), drained and rinsed, and cook for 2-3 minutes to heat through.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,4,'Add diced tomatoes (fresh or canned) to the skillet and cook for another 3-4 minutes until slightly softened.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,5,'Season with salt, black pepper, and dried Italian herbs (such as basil, oregano, and thyme) to taste.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,6,'Add fresh spinach leaves to the skillet and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,7,'Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(7,8,'Serve the white beans, tomatoes, and spinach hot as a side dish or a light meal.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,1,'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,2,'Add spaghetti pasta to the boiling water and cook according to the package instructions until al dente.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,3,'While the pasta is cooking, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,4,'Add minced garlic to the skillet and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,5,'Pour canned marinara sauce into the skillet and bring to a simmer.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,6,'Season the marinara sauce with salt, black pepper, and dried Italian herbs (such as basil, oregano, and thyme) to taste.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,7,'Let the sauce simmer for about 5-10 minutes to allow the flavors to meld together.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,8,'Once the pasta is cooked, drain it and add it to the skillet with the marinara sauce.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,9,'Toss the pasta with the sauce until well coated.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(8,10,'Serve the quick and easy spaghetti with marinara sauce hot, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese and chopped fresh basil if desired.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,1,'Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,2,'In a large mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,3,'Add cold, cubed butter to the dry ingredients and use a pastry cutter or your fingers to cut the butter into the flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,4,'In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs and heavy cream.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,5,'Pour the egg and cream mixture into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Be careful not to overmix.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,6,'Gently fold in any additional ingredients you would like, such as dried fruit, chocolate chips, or nuts.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,7,'Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead it gently a few times until it comes together.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,8,'Pat the dough into a circle about 1 inch (2.5 cm) thick. Use a round cutter to cut out scones or use a knife to cut the dough into wedges.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,9,'Place the scones onto the prepared baking sheet, leaving some space between each one.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,10,'Brush the tops of the scones with a little heavy cream for a golden finish.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,11,'Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the scones are golden brown and cooked through.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(9,12,'Remove from the oven and let the scones cool on a wire rack for a few minutes before serving.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,1,'Preheat your oven to the highest temperature it can go, typically around 500°F (260°C) or higher.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,2,'Roll out pizza dough on a lightly floured surface to your desired thickness.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,3,'Transfer the rolled-out dough to a baking sheet or pizza stone.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,4,'Spread pizza sauce evenly over the dough, leaving a small border around the edges for the crust.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,5,'Sprinkle shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce, covering the entire pizza.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,6,'Add your desired toppings such as pepperoni, mushrooms, bell peppers, onions, olives, or any other toppings you prefer.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,7,'Optionally, sprinkle some grated Parmesan cheese and dried oregano or basil on top for extra flavor.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,8,'Carefully transfer the pizza to the preheated oven and bake for 10-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly and melted.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,9,'Once the pizza is done, remove it from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(10,10,'Slice the pizza into wedges or squares and serve hot.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,1,'Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over high heat.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,2,'Add thinly sliced protein such as chicken, beef, shrimp, or tofu to the skillet.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,3,'Stir-fry the protein until it is cooked through and nicely browned. Remove from the skillet and set aside.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,4,'In the same skillet, add additional oil if needed and stir-fry chopped vegetables such as bell peppers, broccoli, carrots, snap peas, mushrooms, and onions until they are crisp-tender.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,5,'Add minced garlic and grated ginger to the skillet and stir-fry for another 30 seconds to 1 minute until fragrant.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,6,'Return the cooked protein to the skillet with the vegetables.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,7,'In a small bowl, mix together soy sauce, oyster sauce, hoisin sauce, or any other sauce of your choice.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,8,'Pour the sauce over the stir-fry mixture in the skillet and toss everything together until well coated.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,9,'Cook for another 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly, until the sauce has thickened slightly and everything is heated through.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,10,'Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary, adding salt, pepper, or additional sauce as desired.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(11,11,'Serve the stir-fry hot over cooked rice or noodles.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,1,'In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium heat.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,2,'Add diced onions, carrots, and celery to the pot. Cook until the vegetables are softened, about 5-7 minutes.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,3,'Stir in minced garlic and cook for another 1-2 minutes until fragrant.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,4,'Pour in canned diced tomatoes and chicken or vegetable broth. Bring the mixture to a simmer.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,5,'Add dried Italian herbs such as basil, oregano, and thyme to the pot. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,6,'Once the soup is simmering, add fresh or frozen cheese tortellini to the pot.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,7,'Cook the tortellini according to the package instructions until they are tender and cooked through.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,8,'Stir in fresh spinach leaves until wilted, about 1-2 minutes.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,9,'Taste the soup and adjust seasoning if necessary.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(12,10,'Serve the Rustic Italian Tortellini Soup hot, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese and chopped fresh basil if desired.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,1,'In a large mixing bowl, combine ground beef and ground pork.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,2,'Add finely chopped onions, minced garlic, breadcrumbs, beaten eggs, salt, black pepper, and ground allspice to the bowl.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,3,'Use your hands to mix the ingredients until well combined.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,4,'Shape the meat mixture into small meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,5,'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,6,'Add the meatballs to the skillet in batches, making sure not to overcrowd the pan.','2024-05-06 21:48:53'),(13,7,'Cook the meatb